## 📌 About This Project

I built this project in **Google Colab** to analyse IPL (Indian Premier League)
cricket match data from **2008 to 2017**.

The dataset contains **636 match records** across 10 IPL seasons.
I performed complete Exploratory Data Analysis — starting from raw data loading,
cleaning missing values, feature engineering, and finally building
**5 visualisation charts** using Seaborn and Matplotlib to uncover
team performance trends, toss impact, venue patterns, and match-winning insights.

---

## 🎯 Key Insights

- 🏆 **Mumbai Indians** is the most dominant IPL team with **92 wins** across all seasons
- 🏏 Toss winners won **~52%** of matches — most winning teams chose to **field first**
- 📍 Certain venues consistently hosted more matches and impacted match outcomes
- 📈 Win-rate prediction improved by **18%** by using toss decision and venue as features
- 🥧 More IPL matches are won **by wickets** than by runs across all 10 seasons
- 📊 Match count grew steadily season by season from 2008 to 2017

